BasicHierarchicalStringObjectMap
public class ListHierarchyNode<T>
extends AbstractHierarchyNode<T,ListHierarchyNode<T>>
implements Serializable

A node in a simple hierarchy, where a value of the given generic type is attached at each node. The children are stored in a List and are thus ordered.

registerChild

public void registerChild(ListHierarchyNode<T> child)
Description copied from interface: HierarchyNode
Adds a child node. Does not update the child's parent link! The relationship is primarily owned by the child, so child.setParent() should call this method, not the other way around.
